# Intended to block direct access to raw application source and build config,
# reachable only because Cloudflare Pages deploys the repository root as-is
# (no build step configured). NOT CONFIRMED WORKING as of 2026-07-20 — see
# docs/audit/MASTER_PRODUCTION_CERTIFICATION.md and
# PRODUCTION_INCIDENT_REGISTER.md #8 for the full account. Two live attempts
# both failed:
#   1. Unforced rules (`404`) — real file content still served, unchanged.
#   2. Forced rules (`404!`, current) — still no change, AND a control test
#      against a path with no competing real file (/src/<nonexistent>.tsx)
#      also fell through to the generic SPA-fallback instead of this rule's
#      404. That rules out "existing file wins" as the cause: this file does
#      not appear to be read/applied at all under the current no-build
#      Cloudflare configuration, unlike _headers (confirmed effective,
#      repeatedly, byte-for-byte). Root cause not further diagnosed without
#      Cloudflare dashboard/support access.
# Left in place (harmless either way) because it is expected to become
# effective once Cloudflare is reconfigured to build from source — dist/
# never contains these files under any build outcome, and a standard
# Cloudflare Pages build+deploy is the well-documented, normal way _redirects
# is meant to be consumed. Until then, this file provides NO protection —
# do not treat the source-exposure finding as mitigated.
/src/*               /  404!
/server.ts           /  404!
/vite.config.ts      /  404!
/tsconfig.json       /  404!
/package.json        /  404!
/package-lock.json   /  404!
